Selenium IDE is a record-and-playback tool used for simple test automation without coding, 
while Selenium WebDriver is a programming interface used to automate browsers 
using languages like Java or Python and is mainly used for building advanced automation frameworks.

| Feature                   | Selenium IDE                   | Selenium WebDriver                                  |
| ------------------------- | ------------------------------ | --------------------------------------------------- |
| **Type**                  | Browser extension tool         | Programming API                                     |
| **Coding**                | Coding required nahi hota      | Programming language required hoti hai              |
| **Usage**                 | Record and playback testing    | Full automation framework                           |
| **Flexibility**           | Limited functionality          | Highly flexible                                     |
| **Programming Languages** | Support nahi karta             | Java, Python, C#, JavaScript support karta          |
| **Complex Test Cases**    | Handle nahi kar sakta          | Complex scenarios handle kar sakta                  |
| **Framework Integration** | Possible nahi                  | TestNG, JUnit, Maven ke sath integrate ho sakta hai |
| **Real Project Usage**    | Mostly learning ya small tests | Real industry automation projects                   |
